    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[ABS21] Alon, Noga and Buci\\'c, Matija and Sudakov, Benny, Large cliques and independent sets all over the place. Proc. Amer. Math. Soc. (2021), 3145-3157.\n \n [AlSu07] Alon, Noga and Sudakov, Benny, On graphs with subgraphs having large independence numbers. J. Graph Theory (2007), 149-157.",
      "remarks": "A problem of Erd\\H{o}s and Hajnal, who thought that there is no such graph for $g(n)=(\\log n)^3$. Alon and Sudakov \\cite{AlSu07} proved that there is no such graph with\\[g(n)=\\frac{c}{\\log\\log n}(\\log n)^3\\]for some constant $c>0$.\n\nAlon, Buci\\'{c}, and Sudakov \\cite{ABS21} construct such a graph with\\[g(n)\\leq 2^{2^{(\\log\\log n)^{1/2+o(1)}}}.\\]See also [804]."
    },
